    "heading_text": "Technical Details",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/request-forms/#about-form-fields",
    "chunk_index": 0,
    "chunk_text": "Technical Details. Data from forms is normally encoded using the \"media type\" application/x-www-form-urlencoded . But when the form includes files, it is encoded as multipart/form-data . You'll read about handling files in the next chapter. If you want to read more about these encodings and form fields, head to the MDN web docs for POST .",
